00:26.437 --> 00:29.524
Theorising that one could
time-travel within his own lifetime,

00:29.524 --> 00:32.860
Dr Sam Beckett stepped
into the quantum leap accelerator

00:32.860 --> 00:34.904
and vanished!

00:39.742 --> 00:42.161
He awoke to find himself
trapped in the past.

00:42.161 --> 00:45.832
Facing mirror images
that were not his own...

00:45.832 --> 00:50.002
and driven by an unknown force
to change history for the better.

00:51.087 --> 00:53.589
His only guide on this journey is Al,

00:53.589 --> 00:56.843
an observer from his own time
who appears in the form

00:56.843 --> 01:00.930
of a hologram that only Sam
can see and hear.

01:00.930 --> 01:04.058
And so Dr Beckett finds himself
leaping from life to life,

01:04.058 --> 01:06.978
striving to put right
what once went wrong,

01:06.978 --> 01:09.647
and hoping each time
that his next leap...

01:11.190 --> 01:13.234
..will be the leap home.

01:33.754 --> 01:36.007
No fair thinking about
anything but us.

01:36.007 --> 01:38.134
You promised.

01:38.134 --> 01:40.261
I...

01:40.261 --> 01:42.388
Yeah, I guess I did.

01:42.388 --> 01:44.557
We get so little time together.

01:44.557 --> 01:47.727
I won't have you off
thinking about anything but me.

01:50.813 --> 01:53.232
OK. Medical school.

01:53.232 --> 01:55.568
I won't be jealous
of medical school.

02:08.705 --> 02:12.251
What are you doing here?
Take him any way you want, Papa D.

02:12.251 --> 02:14.295
No!

03:30.538 --> 03:33.207
Ray, no! No!

03:33.207 --> 03:36.043
Make it stop! No!
Lonnie, make it stop!

03:37.128 --> 03:40.339
You make it stop.
They won't listen to me.
I wonder why (!)

03:40.339 --> 03:43.426
Lonnie, please!
Now it's 'Lonnie, please.'

03:43.426 --> 03:46.971
Well, what about when Lonnie said
please stay away from his brother?

03:55.313 --> 03:57.940
I can't stay away from him.
I love him.

04:04.010 --> 04:07.097
Until she gets bored.
Or until it ain't hip no more.

04:07.097 --> 04:10.016
Then what happens to Ray?
Isn't that my business?

04:10.016 --> 04:13.895
Not as long as I'm busting my ass
to put you through med school,
it ain't!

04:13.895 --> 04:16.815
You got your nose so wide open
you forgot what colour you are?

04:16.815 --> 04:19.108
What does colour have to do with it?
Say what?

04:19.108 --> 04:22.821
I think you choked him too long,
Papa D. Or not long enough.

04:22.821 --> 04:24.990
Colour shouldn't have
anything to do...

04:24.990 --> 04:27.033
with relationships.

04:29.369 --> 04:31.830
No-one should know that
better than us.

04:32.831 --> 04:37.085
You been sucking up to this white
trash so long, you starting
to sound like her.

04:37.085 --> 04:40.088
He sounds like your future.
Not MY future.

04:40.088 --> 04:42.841
She's talking about mine.
Doing what?

04:42.841 --> 04:45.343
Dumping Mr Charlie's bedpans?

04:45.343 --> 04:49.014
Yeah, man. Your MD ain't gonna stand
for more than 'moving doo-doo' (!)

04:49.014 --> 04:53.685
Ray's good. He'll be able to
practice anywhere in this country.
He's already breaking barriers.

04:53.685 --> 04:56.855
Do you think that's why Mom and I
busted our asses all these years?

04:56.855 --> 04:58.773
To break honky barriers?

05:02.027 --> 05:04.154
Ray's staying here.

05:04.154 --> 05:06.281
Taking care of his own people.

05:08.950 --> 05:11.077
It makes sense.
What about Boston?

05:11.077 --> 05:14.206
Boston? You're gonna walk away from
an internship at Brigham?

05:14.206 --> 05:17.375
Uh...
You never said nothing about Boston.

05:17.375 --> 05:19.503
Uh, I must've forgot to tell you.

05:19.503 --> 05:22.297
No. What you forgot
 is who you are!

05:24.216 --> 05:26.218
And we both know why!

05:28.011 --> 05:31.056
You're my brother, man,
and I love you.

05:32.182 --> 05:34.559
But she goes, Ray.

05:34.559 --> 05:36.686
She goes!

05:36.686 --> 05:38.855
And you stay!

05:55.690 --> 05:58.110
This is Melvin the Magnificent.

05:58.110 --> 06:02.155
And I know this heat's got all y'all
hurting' so bad.

06:02.155 --> 06:05.784
Have mercy on LA.
It's another hot one.

06:05.784 --> 06:09.871
Weatherman says it's over 100
and it's gonna stay that way.

06:09.871 --> 06:13.667
So I think, if we've gotta be
sweating all night,

06:13.667 --> 06:18.088
let it be in the arms
of the one you love. That's L-U-V.

06:18.088 --> 06:22.217
Right now, it's 8:25
and the last little bit

06:22.217 --> 06:25.387
of summer sunshine
is about to fall into the sea.

06:25.387 --> 06:28.765
And I, Melvin the Magnificent,
wanna have a word

06:28.765 --> 06:32.769
with all you fine people out there
in partyland.

06:32.769 --> 06:36.231
Now, get yourself
up close to the radio,

06:36.231 --> 06:40.026
cos I'm about to give you your
party instructions for the night.

06:40.026 --> 06:42.195
The first thing you wanna do

06:42.195 --> 06:44.906
is turn the lights
to red, green and blue.

06:44.906 --> 06:48.243
Then, when the moon is bright
and the moon is low,

06:48.243 --> 06:53.331
take your rhythm down
to a time that's real slow.

06:53.331 --> 06:55.375
(RADIO OFF)

06:59.463 --> 07:01.590
Susan...
Ray.

07:01.590 --> 07:04.634
No-one has the right to tell you
what to do with your life.

07:05.719 --> 07:08.388
Not Lonnie, not your mom and not me.

07:12.225 --> 07:14.352
I just wanna be part of your future.

07:14.352 --> 07:16.521
And it's not in Watts.

07:16.521 --> 07:19.983
Lonnie reminds me of that
every time I look in his eyes.

07:24.154 --> 07:26.198
I love you.

07:27.574 --> 07:29.951
And I won't spend my life
without you.

07:42.005 --> 07:43.131
Susan!

07:50.263 --> 07:53.266
You told me this was over.
We were studying and -

07:53.266 --> 07:56.478
I asked you to stay away from
my daughter. Now I'm telling you.

07:56.478 --> 07:59.314
I think -
I don't give a damn what you think.

07:59.314 --> 08:02.818
You just stay away from Susan.
Stop it, Daddy! Not under my roof.

08:02.818 --> 08:05.821
Then I'll move in with Ray!
No, wait a minute. Don't you think

08:05.821 --> 08:09.616
we should talk about this?
You don't want me to move in?
No, I didn't say that.

08:09.616 --> 08:13.078
He doesn't want you in Watts
any more than I do.
I didn't say that either!

08:13.078 --> 08:16.331
You stay away from him and
you stay outta that damn ghetto!

08:16.331 --> 08:18.875
I work there!
Susan.

08:18.875 --> 08:22.504
Coloureds are beating whites
in Watts right now.

08:22.504 --> 08:26.842
You think they won't
turn on you because you volunteered
for a couple of months?

08:26.842 --> 08:29.469
No! Because it's the 20th century!

08:29.469 --> 08:34.182
Because this is Los Angeles,
California. Not Redneck,
Mississippi 100 years ago!

08:34.182 --> 08:38.687
Negroes and whites
are getting married all the time.
It doesn't matter any more.

08:38.687 --> 08:41.690
It does to me.

08:41.690 --> 08:43.942
Now get in the house.

08:46.028 --> 08:49.573
Come on, Susan...
We'll work this out.

08:49.573 --> 08:53.285
The hell you will.
Go in the house, Susan. Please.

08:58.457 --> 09:02.377
Daddy. The only difference
between you and Lonnie
is the colour of your skin!

09:14.306 --> 09:16.516
When you first started
coming around here...

09:17.893 --> 09:20.020
..I tried...

09:20.020 --> 09:22.689
to deal with you as an individual.

09:22.689 --> 09:26.234
But then I realised I have to
deal with you for what you are.

09:28.028 --> 09:30.447
A coloured man
who's going to hurt my daughter.

09:30.447 --> 09:32.741
I'd never hurt Susan.

09:32.741 --> 09:34.910
But they will.
They?

09:34.910 --> 09:36.703
Your brothers...

09:36.703 --> 09:39.122
as that fanatic Malcolm X calls them.

09:39.122 --> 09:41.166
They will hurt her.

09:42.292 --> 09:44.836
And there won't be a thing
you'll be able to do to stop it.

09:58.016 --> 10:00.060
